title: Naulochos/Templum Iovis?
description: A seaside settlement of ancient Thrace that was a colony of Mesembria. Romans referred to the site as Templum Iovis, although Pliny the Elder refers to it as "Tetranaulochus."

properties.description: coordinates after Wikipedia; verified in Google Earth 2013.
